Dark Arena was designed to be ideal for clan competitions and tournaments. Rush to the top story arena where it's well-lit... Meet your enemies head-on, running for the over-loaded M4's and AK-47's in the mid-section, or rush up to the platforms to get one of the AWPs. OR... Go down into the lower levels, where it's pitch-black. Equip your flashlight and go hunting for more specific weapons. Hide in the darkness to surprise unsuspecting people on a scavenger hunt for guns. TIPS
  • You don't start with a knife, but knives are hidden throughout the map!
  • Try shooting off the locker doors in the locker room and see what you find!
  • If rushing up to the arena, throw grenades up to the opposite platform quickly - blow away their AWPs before they can reach them! Careful, you might just end up shooting an AWP right into someone's hands smile
  • Shoot the glass windows in the middle of the arena! Send the explosive barrels rolling down until they drop through the vertical passages into the room below. Drop in a grenade or shoot one barrel, the rest go off, and anyone camping down in that room is blown to bits!
  • Also, if someone is crossing on either side of the arena, release the explosive barrels and ignite them right in front of the guy! Either way, you get credit for barrel kills!
I think it isn't that bad at all for a first map :D

This map is a stealth map which means everything will be dark. Everyone is given a USP and knife. There is no buy zone.

Spawn points are separated so don't expect the help of your teammates straight away. There are some boxes and vending machines to hide behind.
Make sure (if your host) mp_flashlight 1 is on!!! Also i recommend less than 8 players so you can sneak more.

Note: I know that there i no prop for the light because i thought it wasn't necessary for it is just to help guide the player.

German:
Ein kleines Stargate (SG 1) ähnliche map mit 3 Stargates und ein Ringportal Verbund.
CT Startet in eine Wüsten Welt was gleichzeitig Bombenplatz B ist. T Startet im Haus im Walde mit Geiseln. Der „Stargate“ Raum ist Bombenplatz A und Geisel Ziel Ort. Im Wald sind 3 Tarnbüsche die man aufheben kann sowie ein Ringportal spot zum Haus, quasi Fluchttunnel von den Ts. 

Diese Version ist noch als Beta zu sehen, da ich leider kein Server zur Verfügung hatte um die map mit mehreren Teilnehmern zu spielen. Anzahl der max. Spieler ist momentan 20. 

die schwarzen kugeln sind notfall button auf die man schießen kann falls man im Zwischenraum nicht weiter teleportiert wird. Es gibt auf jeder Seite 10 ziel punkte (vor dem Tor) die per Zufall herausgepickt werden um das verkeilen zu vermeiden.

Für Verbesserungsvorschläge bin ich immer offen.
